###AI Interaction Protocol
Refer to vision.md as the absolute Source of Truth. If a proposed design element, code change, or UI adjustment conflicts with any of the 8 Core Pillars (specifically Mechanical Integrity, Visual Continuity, or Radical Visibility), you MUST:
Flag the conflict to the user immediately.
Explain which Pillar is being violated.
Propose an alternative solution that satisfies the user's functional goal while remaining compliant with the Pillars.


###Core Design Pillars
The system is built upon eight fundamental principles that guide all interaction and logic development.
Pillar
Requirement
1. Mechanical Integrity
Exact adherence to Palladium percentile systems, S.D.C./M.D.C. scaling, and Melee Round timing.
2. Megaversal Bridge
Setting-agnostic architecture allows interaction between Fantasy, Rifts, Heroes Unlimited, and Nightbane.
3. Speed Over Spectacle
Primary combat stats accessible in two taps or less. Minimized menu-diving during active play.
4. Total GM Agency
All calculated values are inspectable and overrideable to accommodate homebrew and narrative needs.
5. Physical Dice Priority
Prioritizes manual entry of physical dice results via frictionless numeric input flows.
6. Visual Continuity
Anchored UI elements ensure players never lose their bearings when swapping states.
7. Intuitive Depth
Surface-level results for speed, with deep math and rule references accessible via tap-to-expand.
8. Radical Visibility
Unless explicitly directed, choices are never hidden. Restricted options are grayed out with a visible explanation of why they are unavailable.
9. Sophisticated Calculator
The app is strictly a tool for taking the friction out of playing at a table. It is NOT a video game that plays Palladium for you.

###Core guidelines
If a content schema is updated, update the associated example json to account for the update. Do not create new example jsons of that data type, always update the base example json so we have all examples in one file.

### Content catalog layout
When adding, moving, or reorganizing JSON under `src/data/content/`, follow **`docs/content-catalog-layout.md`**. **Ancillary** JSON (registries, cross-lists, progression documents, genre category maps, global rules) that supports a primary catalog belongs in **`<catalog-dir>/utils/`** — not beside row pools at the catalog root. Documented root exceptions (e.g. `skills/hand_to_hand.json`, `skills/weapon_proficiencies.json`) stay at the folder root. Update `palladiumSchemaPaths.ts`, loaders, and `validate-palladium-schemas.mjs` when paths change.

### Documentation sync (behavior & workflow changes)
When a change alters **how the app works** — loaders, forge tabs, creation flow, catalog layout, validation commands, ingest workflow, engine contracts, or user-visible creation/spawn behavior — **update the relevant docs in the same PR/session as the code**. Use the checklist in **`docs/gemini-project-context.md`** § Development workflow. Do not rely on chat history alone; future agents read the repo docs.

### Nightbane talent catalog ingest
When adding, updating, or auditing Nightbane Talents (`src/data/content/talents/`), follow **`docs/ingest/talents.md`** (Pass A/B workflow, form rules, P.P.E., batch template, validation commands). Keep that doc updated when ingest rules change; flag mechanics ambiguity and ask the user for a ruling before encoding.

### Palladium skill catalog ingest
When adding, updating, or auditing skills (`src/data/content/skills/`), follow **`docs/ingest/skills.md`** (Pass A/B workflow, category files, prerequisites, trait lists, batch template, validation commands). Keep that doc updated when ingest rules change; flag mechanics ambiguity and ask the user for a ruling before encoding.

### Palladium magic catalog ingest
When adding, updating, or auditing magic (`src/data/content/magic/`), follow **`docs/ingest/magic.md`** (Pass A/B workflow, school files, cross-lists, batch template). Keep that doc updated when ingest rules change; flag mechanics ambiguity and ask the user for a ruling before encoding.

### Palladium psionic catalog ingest
When adding, updating, or auditing psionics (`src/data/content/psionics/`), follow **`docs/ingest/psionics.md`** (Pass A/B workflow, category files, genrePlacements, batch template). Keep that doc updated when ingest rules change; flag mechanics ambiguity and ask the user for a ruling before encoding.

### Palladium O.C.C. catalog ingest
When adding, updating, or auditing O.C.C.s (`src/data/content/occs/<genre>/`), follow **`docs/ingest/occs.md`** (Pass A/B workflow, genre folders + book files, XP table links, Shadow O.C.C. pairing). Keep that doc updated when ingest rules change; flag mechanics ambiguity and ask the user for a ruling before encoding.

### Palladium race catalog ingest
When adding, updating, or auditing races (`src/data/content/races/`), follow **`docs/ingest/races.md`** (Pass A/B workflow, audience pools, genre whitelist, R.C.C. pairing). Keep that doc updated when ingest rules change; flag mechanics ambiguity and ask the user for a ruling before encoding.

### Nightbane Morphus trait ingest
When adding, updating, or auditing Morphus trait tables (`src/data/content/morphus/tables/`) or running the PDF pipeline (`src/data/source/morphus-ingest/`), follow **`docs/ingest/morphus.md`** (Pass A/B workflow, hub/leaf layout, non-playable row rules, validation commands). Encoding details: **`docs/morphus_authoring.md`**. Keep the ingest playbook updated when conventions change; flag mechanics ambiguity and ask the user for a ruling before encoding.

### Palladium XP progression ingest
When adding, updating, or auditing XP tables (`src/data/content/progression/xp_tables/`), follow **`docs/ingest/xp_tables.md`** (floor transcription, book bundles, O.C.C. bidirectional links). Coordinate with **`docs/ingest/occs.md`** when linking `progression.xpTableId`. Keep that doc updated when ingest rules change; flag mechanics ambiguity and ask the user for a ruling before encoding.

### Palladium Hand-to-Hand ingest
When adding, updating, or auditing Hand-to-Hand styles (`src/data/content/skills/hand_to_hand.json`), follow **`docs/ingest/hth.md`** (level 1–15 progression matrix, `hth_*` ids). Coordinate O.C.C. `handToHandRules` via **`docs/ingest/occs.md`**. Keep that doc updated when ingest rules change; flag mechanics ambiguity and ask the user for a ruling before encoding.

### Palladium weapon proficiency ingest
When adding, updating, or auditing W.P. rows (`src/data/content/skills/weapon_proficiencies.json`) or the shared modern ladder (`skills/utils/standard_modern_weapon_progression.json`), follow **`docs/ingest/weapon_proficiencies.md`**. Coordinate O.C.C. `wpRules` via **`docs/ingest/occs.md`**. Keep that doc updated when ingest rules change; flag mechanics ambiguity and ask the user for a ruling before encoding.
